            "content": "# SNS Publisher Backend — Design Spec\n\n## Overview\n\nAdd an SNS publisher backend to the `shove` crate with full parity to the RabbitMQ publisher. This is the first phase of an SNS+SQS backend — publisher and topology declaration only. The SQS consumer will follow in a separate phase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Module Structure\n\n```\nsrc/backends/\n├── mod.rs              # add: #[cfg(feature = \"sns\")] pub mod sns;\n└── sns/\n    ├── mod.rs          # public re-exports\n    ├── client.rs       # SnsClient wrapper (config, shutdown)\n    ├── publisher.rs    # SnsPublisher (implements Publisher)\n    └── topology.rs     # SnsTopologyDeclarer (implements TopologyDeclarer)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Dependencies & Feature Flag\n\n```toml\nsns = [\n    \"dep:aws-config\",\n    \"dep:aws-sdk-sns\",\n    \"dep:futures\",\n]\n```\n\n- `aws-sdk-sns` — SNS client (publish, create-topic, get-topic-attributes)\n- `aws-config` — shared AWS credential/region resolution\n- `futures` — stream utilities for batch chunking\n\n`aws-sdk-sqs` is deferred to the consumer phase. No other new deps needed.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SnsClient (`client.rs`)\n\nThin wrapper over the AWS SDK client with config and shutdown coordination. Mirrors `RabbitMqClient` API surface.\n\n### Types\n\n```rust\npub struct SnsConfig {\n    pub region: Option<String>,        // None = SDK default chain\n    pub endpoint_url: Option<String>,  // For localstack/testing\n}\n\npub struct SnsClient {\n    client: aws_sdk_sns::Client,\n    shutdown_token: CancellationToken,\n}\n```\n\n### Behavior\n\n- `SnsClient::new(config: &SnsConfig)` — loads AWS config from environment/defaults, applies optional region/endpoint overrides, builds the `sns::Client`\n- No persistent connection management (HTTP-based) — no `is_connected()` needed\n- `shutdown_token()` and `shutdown()` mirror RabbitMQ for consistent API\n- The AWS SDK `sns::Client` is `Clone` and internally manages HTTP/2 connection pooling — a single client is sufficient for concurrent publishing\n\n---\n\n## 4. Topic Resolution & Registry\n\nThe publisher maps `T::topology().queue()` (e.g. `\"order-settlement\"`) to an SNS topic ARN.\n\n### TopicRegistry (internal)\n\n```rust\npub(crate) struct TopicRegistry {\n    arns: RwLock<HashMap<String, String>>,  // queue_name -> ARN\n}\n```\n\nPopulated by the topology declarer or pre-configured ARNs. Not exposed publicly.\n\n### SnsTopicConfig\n\n```rust\npub struct SnsTopicConfig {\n    /// Override ARN for a specific queue name. If absent, topology declarer creates it.\n    pub topic_arns: HashMap<String, String>,\n}\n```\n\n### Consumer Groups Model\n\nConsumer groups map naturally to SNS→SQS fan-out:\n\n- **Single consumer group:** One SQS queue subscribed to the SNS topic. Multiple workers poll the same queue.\n- **Multiple consumer groups:** Multiple SQS queues each subscribed to the same SNS topic. Each group gets every message independently (fan-out).\n- **Filtering per group:** SNS subscription filter policies can route subsets of messages to specific groups.\n\n**Impact on publisher:** None. The publisher publishes to the SNS topic. Consumer group topology (SQS queues + subscriptions) is handled by the topology declarer and future SQS consumer.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SnsPublisher (`publisher.rs`)\n\nImplements the `Publisher` trait.\n\n### Structure\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Clone)]\npub struct SnsPublisher {\n    client: SnsClient,\n    registry: Arc<TopicRegistry>,\n}\n```\n\n### `publish<T>()`\n\n1. Serialize message to JSON\n2. Look up SNS topic ARN from registry via `T::topology().queue()`\n3. If sequenced: set `MessageGroupId` from `T::SEQUENCE_KEY_FN`\n4. For FIFO topics: set `MessageDeduplicationId` (UUID)\n5. Call `sns.publish()` with the payload as the message body\n\n### `publish_with_headers<T>()`\n\n- SNS **message attributes** (string key-value pairs) are the direct analog to AMQP headers\n- Convert `HashMap<String, String>` to SNS `MessageAttributeValue` entries with `DataType: \"String\"`\n\n### `publish_batch<T>()`\n\n- Pre-serialize all messages (fail-fast, same as RabbitMQ)\n- Pre-compute routing keys for sequenced topics\n- Chunk into groups of 10 (SNS `PublishBatch` limit)\n- Send all chunks, collect results\n- Return first error if any chunk fails\n\n### Error Handling\n\n- On publish failure: single retry (mirrors RabbitMQ's one-retry-on-channel-failure pattern)\n- AWS SDK transient errors → `ShoveError::Connection`\n- Serialization errors → `ShoveError::Serialization`\n- No channel pool needed — the SDK client handles concurrency internally\n\n---\n\n## 6. SnsTopologyDeclarer (`topology.rs`)\n\nImplements `TopologyDeclarer`.\n\n### Unsequenced Topics\n\n1. Call `create_topic(name: \"{queue_name}\")` — idempotent, returns ARN if exists\n2. Store ARN in `TopicRegistry`\n\n### Sequenced Topics\n\n1. Call `create_topic(name: \"{queue_name}.fifo\", attributes: { FifoTopic: \"true\", ContentBasedDeduplication: \"true\" })`\n2. FIFO topics enforce per-`MessageGroupId` ordering — maps directly to `SEQUENCE_KEY_FN`\n3. Store ARN in registry\n\n### Pre-existing Topics\n\n- If `SnsTopicConfig.topic_arns` has an entry for the queue name, skip creation\n- Register the provided ARN directly\n- Validate topic exists via `get_topic_attributes()` — fail fast on bad ARN\n\n### Not Created (Deferred to Consumer Phase)\n\n- SQS queues (main, DLQ, hold queues)\n- SNS→SQS subscriptions\n- SQS redrive policies\n\n---\n\n## 7. Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\nLocated in `src/backends/sns/publisher.rs` and `src/backends/sns/topology.rs`:\n\n- Batch chunking logic (messages split into groups of 10, boundary conditions)\n- Topic name → SNS name conversion (standard vs FIFO `.fifo` suffix)\n- Message attribute conversion (`HashMap<String, String>` → SNS `MessageAttributeValue`)\n- Sequenced topic routing (`MessageGroupId` set correctly from `SEQUENCE_KEY_FN`)\n- Error mapping (AWS SDK errors → `ShoveError` variants)\n- Topic registry lookup (hit, miss, pre-configured ARN)\n\n### Integration Tests\n\nLocated in `tests/sns_integration.rs`, using **LocalStack** via testcontainers:\n\n```rust\nstruct TestBroker {\n    container: ContainerAsync<LocalStack>,\n    endpoint_url: String,\n}\n```\n\nTest cases (mirroring `rabbitmq_integration.rs` structure):\n\n- **Publish single message:** publish → create temp SQS subscription → verify message received\n- **Publish with headers:** verify message attributes arrive on SQS side\n- **Publish batch:** verify all messages received, test exact boundary (10), test >10 chunking\n- **Sequenced publish:** verify `MessageGroupId` set, FIFO ordering preserved\n- **Topology declaration:** standard topic created, FIFO topic created, pre-existing ARN accepted\n- **Error cases:** publish to non-existent topic, invalid ARN config\n\nSQS subscriptions in integration tests are for verification only — created in the test harness to prove messages land correctly, not part of the library's publisher scope.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Public API Surface\n\n### `src/backends/sns/mod.rs`\n\n```rust\npub use client::{SnsClient, SnsConfig};\npub use publisher::SnsPublisher;\npub use topology::SnsTopologyDeclarer;\n```\n\n### `src/lib.rs` (behind feature gate)\n\n```rust\n#[cfg(feature = \"sns\")]\npub use backends::sns::{SnsClient, SnsConfig, SnsPublisher, SnsTopologyDeclarer};\n```\n\n### User-Facing Usage\n\n```rust\nlet client = SnsClient::new(&SnsConfig {\n    region: None,\n    endpoint_url: None,\n}).await?;\n\nlet declarer = SnsTopologyDeclarer::new(client.clone());\ndeclare_topic::<MyTopic>(&declarer).await?;\n\nlet publisher = SnsPublisher::new(client);\npublisher.publish::<MyTopic>(&my_message).await?;\n```\n",
