            "content": "# SQS Consumer Backend Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Add an SQS consumer backend with full parity to the RabbitMQ consumer, including consumer groups and autoscaling.\n\n**Architecture:** `SqsConsumer` implements the `Consumer` trait by long-polling SQS queues. Outcomes map to SQS operations: Ack→DeleteMessage, Retry→ChangeMessageVisibility, Reject→DeleteMessage (SQS native redrive handles DLQ). The topology declarer is extended to create SQS queues with redrive policies and SNS subscriptions. Consumer groups and autoscaler mirror the RabbitMQ pattern with an SQS-specific `QueueStatsProvider`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** `aws-sdk-sqs`, `aws-sdk-sns`, `aws-config`, `tokio`, `serde_json`. Integration tests use LocalStack via `testcontainers-modules`.\n\n**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-02-sqs-consumer-design.md`\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n| Action | Path | Responsibility |\n|--------|------|----------------|\n| Modify | `Cargo.toml` | Move `aws-sdk-sqs` from dev-dep to optional dep in `sns` feature |\n| Modify | `src/backends/sns/client.rs` | Add SQS client accessor to `SnsClient` |\n| Modify | `src/backends/sns/topology.rs` | Add `QueueRegistry`, extend declarer for SQS queues + SNS subscriptions |\n| Modify | `src/backends/sns/publisher.rs` | Add `shard` message attribute for sequenced topics |\n| Create | `src/backends/sns/router.rs` | Outcome routing: delete, visibility change |\n| Create | `src/backends/sns/consumer.rs` | `SqsConsumer` implementing `Consumer` trait |\n| Create | `src/backends/sns/consumer_group.rs` | `SqsConsumerGroup` — mirrors RabbitMQ ConsumerGroup |\n| Create | `src/backends/sns/registry.rs` | `SqsConsumerGroupRegistry` |\n| Create | `src/backends/sns/stats.rs` | `SqsQueueStatsProvider` implementing `QueueStatsProvider` |\n| Modify | `src/backends/sns/mod.rs` | Add new modules |\n| Modify | `src/lib.rs` | Extend `sns` re-exports |\n| Create | `tests/sns_sqs_integration.rs` | Integration tests |\n| Modify | `README.md` | Update SNS/SQS status |\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Dependencies and SnsClient SQS Extension\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `Cargo.toml`\n- Modify: `src/backends/sns/client.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Move aws-sdk-sqs to optional dep and add to sns feature**\n\nIn `Cargo.toml`:\n\nChange the `sns` feature to:\n```toml\nsns = [\"dep:aws-config\", \"dep:aws-sdk-sns\", \"dep:aws-sdk-sqs\"]\n```\n\nMove `aws-sdk-sqs` from `[dev-dependencies]` to `[dependencies]`:\n```toml\naws-sdk-sqs = { version = \"1\", optional = true }\n```\n\nRemove the `aws-sdk-sqs = \"1\"` line from `[dev-dependencies]` (it's now a regular dep).\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Extend SnsClient to hold an SQS client**\n\nIn `src/backends/sns/client.rs`, update the struct and constructor:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Clone)]\npub struct SnsClient {\n    sns_client: aws_sdk_sns::Client,\n    sqs_client: aws_sdk_sqs::Client,\n    shutdown_token: CancellationToken,\n}\n\nimpl SnsClient {\n    pub async fn new(config: &SnsConfig) -> Result<Self> {\n        let mut aws_config = aws_config::from_env();\n\n        if let Some(region) = &config.region {\n            aws_config = aws_config.region(aws_config::Region::new(region.clone()));\n        }\n        if let Some(endpoint) = &config.endpoint_url {\n            aws_config = aws_config.endpoint_url(endpoint);\n        }\n\n        let aws_config = aws_config.load().await;\n\n        let sns_client = aws_sdk_sns::Client::new(&aws_config);\n        let sqs_client = aws_sdk_sqs::Client::new(&aws_config);\n\n        Ok(Self {\n            sns_client,\n            sqs_client,\n            shutdown_token: CancellationToken::new(),\n        })\n    }\n\n    /// Return a reference to the underlying AWS SDK SNS client.\n    pub(crate) fn inner(&self) -> &aws_sdk_sns::Client {\n        &self.sns_client\n    }\n\n    /// Return a reference to the underlying AWS SDK SQS client.\n    pub(crate) fn sqs(&self) -> &aws_sdk_sqs::Client {\n        &self.sqs_client\n    }\n\n    // shutdown_token() and shutdown() unchanged\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify it compiles and existing tests pass**\n\nRun: `cargo -q check --features sns`\nRun: `cargo -q test --features sns --lib backends::sns::client`\nExpected: 3 tests pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add Cargo.toml src/backends/sns/client.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(sns): add SQS client to SnsClient\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: QueueRegistry and Topology Declarer SQS Extension\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/backends/sns/topology.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add QueueRegistry**\n\nAdd to `src/backends/sns/topology.rs` (after `TopicRegistry`):\n\n```rust\n/// Registry mapping queue names to SQS queue URLs.\n///\n/// Populated by the topology declarer. Shared with the consumer via `Arc`.\npub struct QueueRegistry {\n    urls: RwLock<HashMap<String, String>>,\n}\n\nimpl Default for QueueRegistry {\n    fn default() -> Self {\n        Self::new()\n    }\n}\n\nimpl QueueRegistry {\n    pub fn new() -> Self {\n        Self {\n            urls: RwLock::new(HashMap::new()),\n        }\n    }\n\n    pub async fn get(&self, queue_name: &str) -> Option<String> {\n        self.urls.read().await.get(queue_name).cloned()\n    }\n\n    pub async fn insert(&self, queue_name: String, url: String) {\n        self.urls.write().await.insert(queue_name, url);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Extend SnsTopologyDeclarer with SQS queue creation**\n\nUpdate `SnsTopologyDeclarer` to accept an optional `QueueRegistry` and add SQS methods:\n\n```rust\npub struct SnsTopologyDeclarer {\n    client: SnsClient,\n    topic_registry: Arc<TopicRegistry>,\n    queue_registry: Option<Arc<QueueRegistry>>,\n}\n\nimpl SnsTopologyDeclarer {\n    pub fn new(client: SnsClient, registry: Arc<TopicRegistry>) -> Self {\n        Self {\n            client,\n            topic_registry: registry,\n            queue_registry: None,\n        }\n    }\n\n    /// Enable SQS queue creation alongside SNS topics.\n    ///\n    /// When set, `declare()` also creates SQS queues, DLQs, and SNS→SQS subscriptions.\n    pub fn with_queue_registry(mut self, registry: Arc<QueueRegistry>) -> Self {\n        self.queue_registry = Some(registry);\n        self\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThen add internal methods for SQS queue creation:\n\n```rust\nimpl SnsTopologyDeclarer {\n    // ... existing methods (update `self.registry` references to `self.topic_registry`) ...\n\n    /// Create an SQS queue with optional redrive policy, return queue URL and ARN.\n    async fn create_sqs_queue(\n        &self,\n        queue_name: &str,\n        fifo: bool,\n        dlq_arn: Option<&str>,\n        max_receive_count: u32,\n    ) -> Result<(String, String)> {\n        let mut req = self.client.sqs().create_queue().queue_name(queue_name);\n\n        if fifo {\n            req = req\n                .attributes(aws_sdk_sqs::types::QueueAttributeName::FifoQueue, \"true\")\n                .attributes(aws_sdk_sqs::types::QueueAttributeName::ContentBasedDeduplication, \"true\");\n        }\n\n        if let Some(dlq_arn) = dlq_arn {\n            let redrive_policy = format!(\n                r#\"{{\"deadLetterTargetArn\":\"{}\",\"maxReceiveCount\":\"{}\"}}\"#,\n                dlq_arn, max_receive_count\n            );\n            req = req.attributes(\n                aws_sdk_sqs::types::QueueAttributeName::RedrivePolicy,\n                redrive_policy,\n            );\n        }\n\n        let result = req.send().await.map_err(|e| {\n            ShoveError::Topology(format!(\"failed to create SQS queue '{queue_name}': {e}\"))\n        })?;\n\n        let queue_url = result\n            .queue_url()\n            .ok_or_else(|| ShoveError::Topology(format!(\"SQS queue '{queue_name}' created but no URL returned\")))?\n            .to_string();\n\n        // Get ARN\n        let attrs = self.client.sqs()\n            .get_queue_attributes()\n            .queue_url(&queue_url)\n            .attribute_names(aws_sdk_sqs::types::QueueAttributeName::QueueArn)\n            .send()\n            .await\n            .map_err(|e| ShoveError::Topology(format!(\"failed to get ARN for SQS queue '{queue_name}': {e}\")))?;\n\n        let queue_arn = attrs\n            .attributes()\n            .and_then(|a| a.get(&aws_sdk_sqs::types::QueueAttributeName::QueueArn))\n            .ok_or_else(|| ShoveError::Topology(format!(\"no ARN returned for SQS queue '{queue_name}'\")))?\n            .to_string();\n\n        Ok((queue_url, queue_arn))\n    }\n\n    /// Subscribe an SQS queue to an SNS topic, with optional filter policy.\n    async fn subscribe_sqs_to_sns(\n        &self,\n        topic_arn: &str,\n        queue_arn: &str,\n        queue_url: &str,\n        filter_policy: Option<&str>,\n    ) -> Result<()> {\n        // Set queue policy to allow SNS delivery\n        let policy = format!(\n            r#\"{{\"Statement\":[{{\"Effect\":\"Allow\",\"Principal\":\"*\",\"Action\":\"sqs:SendMessage\",\"Resource\":\"{}\",\"Condition\":{{\"ArnEquals\":{{\"aws:SourceArn\":\"{}\"}}}}}}]}}\"#,\n            queue_arn, topic_arn\n        );\n        self.client.sqs()\n            .set_queue_attributes()\n            .queue_url(queue_url)\n            .attributes(aws_sdk_sqs::types::QueueAttributeName::Policy, policy)\n            .send()\n            .await\n            .map_err(|e| ShoveError::Topology(format!(\"failed to set SQS queue policy: {e}\")))?;\n\n        let mut sub_req = self.client.inner()\n            .subscribe()\n            .topic_arn(topic_arn)\n            .protocol(\"sqs\")\n            .endpoint(queue_arn)\n            .attributes(\"RawMessageDelivery\", \"true\");\n\n        if let Some(fp) = filter_policy {\n            sub_req = sub_req.attributes(\"FilterPolicy\", fp);\n        }\n\n        sub_req.send().await.map_err(|e| {\n            ShoveError::Topology(format!(\"failed to subscribe SQS to SNS: {e}\"))\n        })?;\n\n        Ok(())\n    }\n\n    /// Declare SQS infrastructure for an unsequenced topology.\n    async fn declare_sqs_unsequenced(&self, topology: &QueueTopology, topic_arn: &str) -> Result<()> {\n        let queue_registry = self.queue_registry.as_ref()\n            .ok_or_else(|| ShoveError::Topology(\"queue_registry not set; call with_queue_registry()\".into()))?;\n\n        let fifo = false;\n        let queue_name = topology.queue().to_string();\n\n        // Create DLQ first (if needed)\n        let dlq_arn = if let Some(dlq_name) = topology.dlq() {\n            let (dlq_url, dlq_arn) = self.create_sqs_queue(dlq_name, fifo, None, 0).await?;\n            queue_registry.insert(dlq_name.to_string(), dlq_url).await;\n            Some(dlq_arn)\n        } else {\n            None\n        };\n\n        // Create main queue with redrive\n        let max_receive_count = 10; // Default, overridden by ConsumerOptions at runtime\n        let (queue_url, queue_arn) = self.create_sqs_queue(\n            &queue_name,\n            fifo,\n            dlq_arn.as_deref(),\n            max_receive_count,\n        ).await?;\n\n        // Subscribe to SNS topic\n        self.subscribe_sqs_to_sns(topic_arn, &queue_arn, &queue_url, None).await?;\n\n        queue_registry.insert(queue_name, queue_url).await;\n\n        Ok(())\n    }\n\n    /// Declare SQS infrastructure for a sequenced topology (N sharded FIFO queues).\n    async fn declare_sqs_sequenced(&self, topology: &QueueTopology, topic_arn: &str) -> Result<()> {\n        let queue_registry = self.queue_registry.as_ref()\n            .ok_or_else(|| ShoveError::Topology(\"queue_registry not set; call with_queue_registry()\".into()))?;\n\n        let seq = topology.sequencing()\n            .ok_or_else(|| ShoveError::Topology(\"expected sequencing config\".into()))?;\n\n        // Create DLQ (FIFO for FIFO topics)\n        let dlq_arn = if let Some(dlq_name) = topology.dlq() {\n            let fifo_dlq_name = format!(\"{dlq_name}.fifo\");\n            let (dlq_url, dlq_arn) = self.create_sqs_queue(&fifo_dlq_name, true, None, 0).await?;\n            queue_registry.insert(dlq_name.to_string(), dlq_url).await;\n            Some(dlq_arn)\n        } else {\n            None\n        };\n\n        // Create N shard queues\n        let max_receive_count = 10;\n        for i in 0..seq.routing_shards() {\n            let shard_name = format!(\"{}-seq-{i}.fifo\", topology.queue());\n\n            let (shard_url, shard_arn) = self.create_sqs_queue(\n                &shard_name,\n                true,\n                dlq_arn.as_deref(),\n                max_receive_count,\n            ).await?;\n\n            // Subscribe with filter policy for this shard\n            let filter = format!(r#\"{{\"shard\":[\"{i}\"]}}\"#);\n            self.subscribe_sqs_to_sns(topic_arn, &shard_arn, &shard_url, Some(&filter)).await?;\n\n            queue_registry.insert(format!(\"{}-seq-{i}\", topology.queue()), shard_url).await;\n        }\n\n        Ok(())\n    }\n}\n```\n\nUpdate the `TopologyDeclarer` impl to call SQS methods when `queue_registry` is set:\n\n```rust\nimpl TopologyDeclarer for SnsTopologyDeclarer {\n    async fn declare(&self, topology: &QueueTopology) -> Result<()> {\n        // --- SNS topic creation (existing logic, unchanged) ---\n        let topic_arn = if let Some(arn) = self.topic_registry.get(topology.queue()).await {\n            // Pre-configured ARN: validate\n            self.client.inner().get_topic_attributes().topic_arn(&arn).send().await\n                .map_err(|e| ShoveError::Topology(format!(\"pre-configured SNS topic ARN '{arn}' is invalid: {e}\")))?;\n            arn\n        } else if topology.sequencing().is_some() {\n            self.declare_fifo(topology).await?;\n            self.topic_registry.get(topology.queue()).await.unwrap()\n        } else {\n            self.declare_standard(topology).await?;\n            self.topic_registry.get(topology.queue()).await.unwrap()\n        };\n\n        // --- SQS queue creation (new, only if queue_registry is set) ---\n        if self.queue_registry.is_some() {\n            if topology.sequencing().is_some() {\n                self.declare_sqs_sequenced(topology, &topic_arn).await?;\n            } else {\n                self.declare_sqs_unsequenced(topology, &topic_arn).await?;\n            }\n        }\n\n        Ok(())\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add unit tests for QueueRegistry**\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn queue_registry_insert_and_get() {\n    let registry = QueueRegistry::new();\n    registry.insert(\"orders\".into(), \"https://sqs.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/123/orders\".into()).await;\n    let url = registry.get(\"orders\").await;\n    assert_eq!(url, Some(\"https://sqs.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/123/orders\".to_string()));\n}\n\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn queue_registry_get_missing() {\n    let registry = QueueRegistry::new();\n    assert_eq!(registry.get(\"nonexistent\").await, None);\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Verify compilation**\n\nRun: `cargo -q check --features sns`\nRun: `cargo -q test --features sns --lib backends::sns::topology`\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/backends/sns/topology.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(sns): extend topology declarer with SQS queue creation\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Publisher Shard Attribute\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/backends/sns/publisher.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add shard attribute for sequenced topics**\n\nIn `publish_single`, after setting `message_group_id`, also compute and set the shard attribute:\n\n```rust\nasync fn publish_single(\n    &self,\n    topic_arn: &str,\n    payload: &str,\n    group_id: Option<&str>,\n    routing_shards: Option<u16>,\n    attributes: Option<HashMap<String, aws_sdk_sns::types::MessageAttributeValue>>,\n) -> Result<()> {\n    let mut req = self.client.inner()\n        .publish()\n        .topic_arn(topic_arn)\n        .message(payload);\n\n    if let Some(gid) = group_id {\n        req = req\n            .message_group_id(gid)\n            .message_deduplication_id(Uuid::new_v4().to_string());\n\n        // Add shard attribute for SNS subscription filter routing\n        if let Some(shards) = routing_shards {\n            let shard = compute_shard(gid, shards);\n            let shard_attr = aws_sdk_sns::types::MessageAttributeValue::builder()\n                .data_type(\"String\")\n                .string_value(shard.to_string())\n                .build()\n                .expect(\"building shard MessageAttributeValue should not fail\");\n            req = req.message_attributes(\"shard\", shard_attr);\n        }\n    }\n\n    if let Some(attrs) = attributes {\n        for (k, v) in attrs {\n            req = req.message_attributes(k, v);\n        }\n    }\n\n    req.send().await\n        .map_err(|e| ShoveError::Connection(format!(\"SNS publish failed: {e}\")))?;\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\nAdd the shard computation function:\n\n```rust\nuse std::hash::{Hash, Hasher};\nuse std::collections::hash_map::DefaultHasher;\n\n/// Compute the shard index for a sequence key.\nfn compute_shard(key: &str, shards: u16) -> u16 {\n    let mut hasher = DefaultHasher::new();\n    key.hash(&mut hasher);\n    (hasher.finish() % shards as u64) as u16\n}\n```\n\nUpdate `do_publish` to pass `routing_shards`:\n\n```rust\nasync fn do_publish<T: Topic>(&self, message: &T::Message, headers: Option<HashMap<String, String>>) -> Result<()> {\n    // ... existing serialization and group_id logic ...\n\n    let routing_shards = match (topology.sequencing(), &group_id) {\n        (Some(seq), Some(_)) => Some(seq.routing_shards()),\n        _ => None,\n    };\n\n    // ... pass routing_shards to publish_single ...\n}\n```\n\nAlso update `publish_batch` entries to include the shard attribute when sequenced.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Add unit tests for compute_shard**\n\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn compute_shard_deterministic() {\n    let a = compute_shard(\"order-123\", 8);\n    let b = compute_shard(\"order-123\", 8);\n    assert_eq!(a, b);\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn compute_shard_within_range() {\n    for i in 0..100 {\n        let key = format!(\"key-{i}\");\n        let shard = compute_shard(&key, 4);\n        assert!(shard < 4, \"shard {shard} out of range for 4 shards\");\n    }\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn compute_shard_distributes() {\n    let mut counts = [0u32; 8];\n    for i in 0..1000 {\n        let shard = compute_shard(&format!(\"key-{i}\"), 8) as usize;\n        counts[shard] += 1;\n    }\n    // Each shard should get at least some messages (rough distribution check)\n    for (i, count) in counts.iter().enumerate() {\n        assert!(*count > 50, \"shard {i} only got {count} messages out of 1000\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify**\n\nRun: `cargo -q test --features sns --lib backends::sns::publisher`\nRun: `cargo -q check --features sns`\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/backends/sns/publisher.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(sns): add shard attribute for sequenced topic routing\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Outcome Router\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/backends/sns/router.rs`\n- Modify: `src/backends/sns/mod.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Implement the SQS outcome router**\n\nCreate `src/backends/sns/router.rs`:\n\n```rust\nuse std::time::Duration;\n\nuse tracing::{debug, error, warn};\n\nuse crate::error::Result;\nuse crate::topology::QueueTopology;\n\n/// Delete a message from SQS (acknowledge).\npub(crate) async fn route_ack(\n    sqs: &aws_sdk_sqs::Client,\n    queue_url: &str,\n    receipt_handle: &str,\n) {\n    if let Err(e) = sqs\n        .delete_message()\n        .queue_url(queue_url)\n        .receipt_handle(receipt_handle)\n        .send()\n        .await\n    {\n        error!(queue_url, error = %e, \"failed to delete (ack) SQS message\");\n    }\n}\n\n/// Change message visibility timeout for retry with escalating delay.\n///\n/// Uses hold_queues[min(retry_count, len-1)].delay() as the visibility timeout.\n/// Falls back to 0 (immediate redelivery) if no hold queues configured.\npub(crate) async fn route_retry(\n    sqs: &aws_sdk_sqs::Client,\n    queue_url: &str,\n    receipt_handle: &str,\n    topology: &QueueTopology,\n    retry_count: u32,\n) {\n    let delay = if topology.hold_queues().is_empty() {\n        Duration::ZERO\n    } else {\n        let index = (retry_count as usize).min(topology.hold_queues().len() - 1);\n        topology.hold_queues()[index].delay()\n    };\n\n    let timeout_secs = delay.as_secs() as i32;\n\n    debug!(\n        queue_url,\n        retry_count,\n        timeout_secs,\n        \"changing visibility for retry\"\n    );\n\n    if let Err(e) = sqs\n        .change_message_visibility()\n        .queue_url(queue_url)\n        .receipt_handle(receipt_handle)\n        .visibility_timeout(timeout_secs)\n        .send()\n        .await\n    {\n        warn!(queue_url, error = %e, \"failed to change visibility for retry\");\n    }\n}\n\n/// Delete a message (reject). SQS native redrive handles DLQ routing\n/// based on receive count.\npub(crate) async fn route_reject(\n    sqs: &aws_sdk_sqs::Client,\n    queue_url: &str,\n    receipt_handle: &str,\n) {\n    // For SQS with native redrive, rejection means letting the message\n    // exceed maxReceiveCount. We change visibility to 0 so it becomes\n    // available immediately and increments receive count faster.\n    // However, if the receive count is already at max, SQS moves it to DLQ.\n    //\n    // Actually, the simplest approach: just let the visibility timeout expire.\n    // Don't delete the message. SQS will redeliver it, and once\n    // ApproximateReceiveCount exceeds maxReceiveCount, it goes to DLQ.\n    //\n    // Set visibility to 0 to speed up the process.\n    if let Err(e) = sqs\n        .change_message_visibility()\n        .queue_url(queue_url)\n        .receipt_handle(receipt_handle)\n        .visibility_timeout(0)\n        .send()\n        .await\n    {\n        warn!(queue_url, error = %e, \"failed to change visibility for reject\");\n    }\n}\n\n/// Change visibility timeout for defer (no retry count increment).\n/// Uses hold_queues[0].delay() if available, otherwise 0.\npub(crate) async fn route_defer(\n    sqs: &aws_sdk_sqs::Client,\n    queue_url: &str,\n    receipt_handle: &str,\n    topology: &QueueTopology,\n) {\n    let delay = if topology.hold_queues().is_empty() {\n        Duration::ZERO\n    } else {\n        topology.hold_queues()[0].delay()\n    };\n\n    let timeout_secs = delay.as_secs() as i32;\n\n    debug!(queue_url, timeout_secs, \"changing visibility for defer\");\n\n    if let Err(e) = sqs\n        .change_message_visibility()\n        .queue_url(queue_url)\n        .receipt_handle(receipt_handle)\n        .visibility_timeout(timeout_secs)\n        .send()\n        .await\n    {\n        warn!(queue_url, error = %e, \"failed to change visibility for defer\");\n    }\n}\n\n/// Extract retry count from SQS message system attributes.\n/// Uses ApproximateReceiveCount - 1 (first receive = 0 retries).\npub(crate) fn get_retry_count(message: &aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message) -> u32 {\n    message\n        .attributes()\n        .and_then(|attrs| {\n            attrs\n                .get(&aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageSystemAttributeName::ApproximateReceiveCount)\n        })\n        .and_then(|v| v.parse::<u32>().ok())\n        .map(|count| count.saturating_sub(1))\n        .unwrap_or(0)\n}\n\n/// Extract string message attributes from an SQS message.\npub(crate) fn extract_message_attributes(\n    message: &aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message,\n) -> std::collections::HashMap<String, String> {\n    message\n        .message_attributes()\n        .map(|attrs| {\n            attrs\n                .iter()\n                .filter_map(|(k, v)| {\n                    v.string_value().map(|sv| (k.clone(), sv.to_string()))\n                })\n                .collect()\n        })\n        .unwrap_or_default()\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n    use crate::topology::TopologyBuilder;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn retry_delay_with_hold_queues() {\n        let topology = TopologyBuilder::new(\"test\")\n            .hold_queue(Duration::from_secs(5))\n            .hold_queue(Duration::from_secs(30))\n            .hold_queue(Duration::from_secs(120))\n            .build();\n\n        // retry_count 0 → hold_queues[0] = 5s\n        let hqs = topology.hold_queues();\n        assert_eq!(hqs[0.min(hqs.len() - 1)].delay(), Duration::from_secs(5));\n        // retry_count 1 → hold_queues[1] = 30s\n        assert_eq!(hqs[1.min(hqs.len() - 1)].delay(), Duration::from_secs(30));\n        // retry_count 2 → hold_queues[2] = 120s\n        assert_eq!(hqs[2.min(hqs.len() - 1)].delay(), Duration::from_secs(120));\n        // retry_count 5 → hold_queues[2] = 120s (capped)\n        assert_eq!(hqs[5.min(hqs.len() - 1)].delay(), Duration::from_secs(120));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn retry_delay_no_hold_queues() {\n        let topology = TopologyBuilder::new(\"test\").build();\n        assert!(topology.hold_queues().is_empty());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn get_retry_count_from_message() {\n        let msg = aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message::builder()\n            .attributes(\n                aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageSystemAttributeName::ApproximateReceiveCount,\n                \"3\",\n            )\n            .build();\n        assert_eq!(get_retry_count(&msg), 2); // 3 - 1 = 2\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn get_retry_count_first_receive() {\n        let msg = aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message::builder()\n            .attributes(\n                aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageSystemAttributeName::ApproximateReceiveCount,\n                \"1\",\n            )\n            .build();\n        assert_eq!(get_retry_count(&msg), 0); // 1 - 1 = 0\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn get_retry_count_missing() {\n        let msg = aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message::builder().build();\n        assert_eq!(get_retry_count(&msg), 0);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn extract_message_attributes_works() {\n        let attr = aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageAttributeValue::builder()\n            .data_type(\"String\")\n            .string_value(\"trace-123\")\n            .build()\n            .unwrap();\n        let msg = aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message::builder()\n            .message_attributes(\"x-trace-id\", attr)\n            .build();\n        let attrs = extract_message_attributes(&msg);\n        assert_eq!(attrs.get(\"x-trace-id\"), Some(&\"trace-123\".to_string()));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn extract_message_attributes_empty() {\n        let msg = aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message::builder().build();\n        let attrs = extract_message_attributes(&msg);\n        assert!(attrs.is_empty());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Add module to mod.rs**\n\nAdd `pub(crate) mod router;` to `src/backends/sns/mod.rs`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify**\n\nRun: `cargo -q test --features sns --lib backends::sns::router`\nExpected: 7 tests pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/backends/sns/router.rs src/backends/sns/mod.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(sns): implement SQS outcome router\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: SqsConsumer — Concurrent Consumption\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/backends/sns/consumer.rs`\n- Modify: `src/backends/sns/mod.rs`\n\nThis is the core consumer. Implements `run`, `run_concurrent`, and `run_dlq`. `run_sequenced` is added in Task 6.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Implement SqsConsumer with concurrent consumption loop**\n\nCreate `src/backends/sns/consumer.rs`. This is the largest file in the plan. Key components:\n\n1. `SqsConsumer` struct holding `SnsClient` and `Arc<QueueRegistry>`\n2. `poll_messages()` — long-polls SQS with `WaitTimeSeconds=5`, `MaxNumberOfMessages=min(10, slots_available)`\n3. `consume_loop_concurrent()` — main loop with `VecDeque<PendingMessage>` for in-order ack\n4. `run_with_reconnect()` —