outer missing-queue scenarios\n\nThe SQS router has the same gaps: no warning when rejecting without DLQ (SQS will cycle the message forever), and no warning when retrying with `Duration::ZERO` because no hold queues exist.\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/backends/sns/router.rs:21-52` — add warning in retry when no hold queues\n- Modify: `src/backends/sns/router.rs:57-68` — add topology param and warning when no DLQ\n- Modify: `src/backends/sns/consumer.rs` — update `route_reject` call sites with topology\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `warn!` in `route_retry` when no hold queues**\n\nIn `src/backends/sns/router.rs`, change the `route_retry` function's empty-hold-queues branch:\n\n```rust\n    let delay = if topology.hold_queues().is_empty() {\n        Duration::ZERO\n    } else {\n```\n\nto:\n\n```rust\n    let delay = if topology.hold_queues().is_empty() {\n        warn!(\n            queue_url,\n            \"retrying message but no hold queues configured — visibility timeout set to 0\"\n        );\n        Duration::ZERO\n    } else {\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Add topology param to `route_reject` and log warning when no DLQ**\n\nChange `route_reject` from:\n\n```rust\npub(crate) async fn route_reject(sqs: &aws_sdk_sqs::Client, queue_url: &str, receipt_handle: &str) {\n```\n\nto:\n\n```rust\npub(crate) async fn route_reject(\n    sqs: &aws_sdk_sqs::Client,\n    queue_url: &str,\n    receipt_handle: &str,\n    topology: &QueueTopology,\n) {\n    if topology.dlq().is_none() {\n        warn!(\n            queue_url,\n            \"rejecting message on queue with no DLQ configured — message will cycle until SQS retention expires\"\n        );\n    }\n```\n\nThe rest of the function body stays the same.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Update all `route_reject` call sites in `src/backends/sns/consumer.rs`**\n\nEvery call to `router::route_reject(sqs, queue_url, &receipt_handle).await` must become `router::route_reject(sqs, queue_url, &receipt_handle, topology).await`.\n\nFind all call sites:\n