            "content": "# SNS/SQS Integration Test Coverage Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Bring SNS/SQS integration test coverage to parity with the 51-test RabbitMQ suite, covering consumer, consumer groups, registry, retry/reject/defer routing, sequenced FIFO processing, DLQ handling, graceful shutdown, handler timeout, deserialization failures, and queue stats.\n\n**Architecture:** Create a new `tests/sns_sqs_integration.rs` test file (requires `aws-sns-sqs` feature) with a shared `TestBroker` harness that spins up LocalStack via testcontainers. Each test gets a fresh LocalStack container. Tests use the full shove public API — `SnsClient`, `SnsTopologyDeclarer` with `QueueRegistry`, `SqsConsumer`, `SqsConsumerGroup`, `SqsConsumerGroupRegistry`, and `SqsQueueStatsProvider`. The SNS publisher is used to inject messages; SQS is polled directly for DLQ verification.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust, tokio, testcontainers (LocalStack), aws-sdk-sns, aws-sdk-sqs, serde_json\n\n**Coverage target:** ~34 new integration tests organized in 12 tasks.\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n| Action | Path | Responsibility |\n|--------|------|----------------|\n| Create | `tests/sns_sqs_integration.rs` | All SNS/SQS consumer integration tests |\n| Modify | `Cargo.toml` | Add `[[test]]` entry for new test |\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Test Harness & Cargo Setup\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `Cargo.toml:85-88` (add test entry)\n- Create: `tests/sns_sqs_integration.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add test entry to Cargo.toml**\n\nAppend after the existing `[[test]]` block:\n\n```toml\n[[test]]\nname = \"sns_sqs_integration\"\nrequired-features = [\"aws-sns-sqs\"]\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Create the test file with harness, imports, and topic definitions**\n\nCreate `tests/sns_sqs_integration.rs`:\n\n```rust\n//! Integration tests for the SNS/SQS consumer backend.\n//!\n//! Each test spins up a fresh LocalStack container via testcontainers, runs\n//! the test, and drops the container on completion (automatic cleanup).\n//!\n//! Run with: `cargo -q test --features aws-sns-sqs --test sns_sqs_integration -- --test-threads=1`\n\nuse std::collections::HashMap;\nuse std::sync::atomic::{AtomicU32, Ordering};\nuse std::sync::Arc;\nuse std::time::Duration;\n\nuse shove::sns::*;\nuse shove::*;\n\nuse testcontainers::runners::AsyncRunner;\nuse testcontainers_modules::localstack::LocalStack;\nuse tokio_util::sync::CancellationToken;\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Test harness\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nstruct TestBroker {\n    #[allow(dead_code)]\n    container: testcontainers::ContainerAsync<LocalStack>,\n    endpoint_url: String,\n}\n\nimpl TestBroker {\n    async fn start() -> Self {\n        let container = LocalStack::default()\n            .start()\n            .await\n            .expect(\"failed to start LocalStack container\");\n\n        let host = container.get_host().await.expect(\"failed to get host\");\n        let port = container\n            .get_host_port_ipv4(4566)\n            .await\n            .expect(\"failed to get LocalStack port\");\n\n        let endpoint_url = format!(\"http://{host}:{port}\");\n\n        // Give LocalStack a moment to initialize SNS/SQS\n        tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(2)).await;\n\n        Self {\n            container,\n            endpoint_url,\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn sns_config(&self) -> SnsConfig {\n        SnsConfig {\n            region: Some(\"us-east-1\".into()),\n            endpoint_url: Some(self.endpoint_url.clone()),\n        }\n    }\n\n    /// Create an SQS client for direct queue verification.\n    async fn sqs_client(&self) -> aws_sdk_sqs::Client {\n        let aws_config = aws_config::from_env()\n            .region(aws_config::Region::new(\"us-east-1\"))\n            .endpoint_url(&self.endpoint_url)\n            .load()\n            .await;\n        aws_sdk_sqs::Client::new(&aws_config)\n    }\n\n    /// Poll SQS directly until `expected_count` messages are received or timeout.\n    async fn receive_messages(\n        &self,\n        sqs_client: &aws_sdk_sqs::Client,\n        queue_url: &str,\n        expected_count: usize,\n        timeout: Duration,\n    ) -> Vec<aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message> {\n        let deadline = tokio::time::Instant::now() + timeout;\n        let mut all_messages = Vec::new();\n\n        while all_messages.len() < expected_count && tokio::time::Instant::now() < deadline {\n            let result = sqs_client\n                .receive_message()\n                .queue_url(queue_url)\n                .max_number_of_messages(10)\n                .wait_time_seconds(1)\n                .message_attribute_names(\"All\")\n                .send()\n                .await\n                .expect(\"failed to receive SQS messages\");\n\n            let msgs = result.messages();\n            all_messages.extend(msgs.iter().cloned());\n        }\n\n        all_messages\n    }\n}\n\n/// Creates a fully wired setup: client, topic_registry, queue_registry, declarer, publisher, consumer.\nstruct TestSetup {\n    client: SnsClient,\n    topic_registry: Arc<TopicRegistry>,\n    queue_registry: Arc<QueueRegistry>,\n    publisher: SnsPublisher,\n    consumer: SqsConsumer,\n}\n\nimpl TestSetup {\n    async fn new(broker: &TestBroker) -> Self {\n        let client = SnsClient::new(&broker.sns_config())\n            .await\n            .expect(\"failed to create SNS client\");\n        let topic_registry = Arc::new(TopicRegistry::new());\n        let queue_registry = Arc::new(QueueRegistry::new());\n        let publisher = SnsPublisher::new(client.clone(), topic_registry.clone());\n        let consumer = SqsConsumer::new(client.clone(), queue_registry.clone());\n\n        Self {\n            client,\n            topic_registry,\n            queue_registry,\n            publisher,\n            consumer,\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn declarer(&self) -> SnsTopologyDeclarer {\n        SnsTopologyDeclarer::new(self.client.clone(), self.topic_registry.clone())\n            .with_queue_registry(self.queue_registry.clone())\n    }\n\n    async fn declare<T: Topic>(&self) {\n        declare_topic::<T>(&self.declarer())\n            .await\n            .expect(\"failed to declare topology\");\n    }\n}\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Test topics\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, serde::Serialize, serde::Deserialize, PartialEq)]\nstruct SimpleMessage {\n    id: String,\n    content: String,\n}\n\ndefine_topic!(\n    WorkTopic,\n    SimpleMessage,\n    TopologyBuilder::new(\"sqs-work\")\n        .dlq()\n        .hold_queue(Duration::from_secs(1))\n        .hold_queue(Duration::from_secs(2))\n        .build()\n);\n\ndefine_topic!(\n    NoDlqTopic,\n    SimpleMessage,\n    TopologyBuilder::new(\"sqs-nodlq\").build()\n);\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, serde::Serialize, serde::Deserialize, PartialEq)]\nstruct OrderMessage {\n    order_id: String,\n    amount: u64,\n}\n\ndefine_sequenced_topic!(\n    SeqSkipTopic,\n    OrderMessage,\n    |msg: &OrderMessage| msg.order_id.clone(),\n    TopologyBuilder::new(\"sqs-seq-skip\")\n        .sequenced(SequenceFailure::Skip)\n        .routing_shards(2)\n        .hold_queue(Duration::from_secs(1))\n        .dlq()\n        .build()\n);\n\ndefine_sequenced_topic!(\n    SeqFailAllTopic,\n    OrderMessage,\n    |msg: &OrderMessage| msg.order_id.clone(),\n    TopologyBuilder::new(\"sqs-seq-failall\")\n        .sequenced(SequenceFailure::FailAll)\n        .routing_shards(2)\n        .hold_queue(Duration::from_secs(1))\n        .dlq()\n        .build()\n);\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Reusable test handlers\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n/// Handler that always returns a fixed outcome.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct FixedOutcomeHandler(Outcome);\n\nimpl MessageHandler<WorkTopic> for FixedOutcomeHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, _msg: SimpleMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        self.0.clone()\n    }\n}\n\n/// Handler that counts invocations and returns Ack.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct CountingHandler {\n    count: Arc<AtomicU32>,\n}\n\nimpl CountingHandler {\n    fn new() -> Self {\n        Self {\n            count: Arc::new(AtomicU32::new(0)),\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn count(&self) -> u32 {\n        self.count.load(Ordering::SeqCst)\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<WorkTopic> for CountingHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, _msg: SimpleMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        self.count.fetch_add(1, Ordering::SeqCst);\n        Outcome::Ack\n    }\n}\n\n/// Handler that returns Reject on first N calls, then Ack.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct RejectThenAckHandler {\n    reject_count: u32,\n    calls: Arc<AtomicU32>,\n}\n\nimpl RejectThenAckHandler {\n    fn new(reject_first_n: u32) -> Self {\n        Self {\n            reject_count: reject_first_n,\n            calls: Arc::new(AtomicU32::new(0)),\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<WorkTopic> for RejectThenAckHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, _msg: SimpleMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        let n = self.calls.fetch_add(1, Ordering::SeqCst);\n        if n < self.reject_count {\n            Outcome::Reject\n        } else {\n            Outcome::Ack\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/// Handler that returns Retry on first N calls, then Ack.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct RetryThenAckHandler {\n    retry_count: u32,\n    calls: Arc<AtomicU32>,\n}\n\nimpl RetryThenAckHandler {\n    fn new(retry_first_n: u32) -> Self {\n        Self {\n            retry_count: retry_first_n,\n            calls: Arc::new(AtomicU32::new(0)),\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn total_calls(&self) -> u32 {\n        self.calls.load(Ordering::SeqCst)\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<WorkTopic> for RetryThenAckHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, _msg: SimpleMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        let n = self.calls.fetch_add(1, Ordering::SeqCst);\n        if n < self.retry_count {\n            Outcome::Retry\n        } else {\n            Outcome::Ack\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/// Handler that sleeps for a configurable duration, then Ack.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct SlowHandler {\n    delay: Duration,\n    calls: Arc<AtomicU32>,\n}\n\nimpl SlowHandler {\n    fn new(delay: Duration) -> Self {\n        Self {\n            delay,\n            calls: Arc::new(AtomicU32::new(0)),\n        }\n    }\n\n    fn total_calls(&self) -> u32 {\n        self.calls.load(Ordering::SeqCst)\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<WorkTopic> for SlowHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, _msg: SimpleMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        self.calls.fetch_add(1, Ordering::SeqCst);\n        tokio::time::sleep(self.delay).await;\n        Outcome::Ack\n    }\n}\n\n/// Handler for sequenced topics that records (order_id, amount) pairs.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct OrderRecordingHandler {\n    records: Arc<tokio::sync::Mutex<Vec<(String, u64)>>>,\n}\n\nimpl OrderRecordingHandler {\n    fn new() -> Self {\n        Self {\n            records: Arc::new(tokio::sync::Mutex::new(Vec::new())),\n        }\n    }\n\n    async fn records(&self) -> Vec<(String, u64)> {\n        self.records.lock().await.clone()\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<SeqSkipTopic> for OrderRecordingHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, msg: OrderMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        self.records\n            .lock()\n            .await\n            .push((msg.order_id.clone(), msg.amount));\n        Outcome::Ack\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<SeqFailAllTopic> for OrderRecordingHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, msg: OrderMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        self.records\n            .lock()\n            .await\n            .push((msg.order_id.clone(), msg.amount));\n        Outcome::Ack\n    }\n}\n\n/// Sequenced handler that rejects messages with a specific order_id.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct RejectOrderHandler {\n    reject_order_id: String,\n    records: Arc<tokio::sync::Mutex<Vec<(String, u64)>>>,\n}\n\nimpl RejectOrderHandler {\n    fn new(reject_order_id: &str) -> Self {\n        Self {\n            reject_order_id: reject_order_id.to_string(),\n            records: Arc::new(tokio::sync::Mutex::new(Vec::new())),\n        }\n    }\n\n    async fn records(&self) -> Vec<(String, u64)> {\n        self.records.lock().await.clone()\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<SeqSkipTopic> for RejectOrderHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, msg: OrderMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        if msg.order_id == self.reject_order_id {\n            Outcome::Reject\n        } else {\n            self.records\n                .lock()\n                .await\n                .push((msg.order_id.clone(), msg.amount));\n            Outcome::Ack\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<SeqFailAllTopic> for RejectOrderHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, msg: OrderMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        if msg.order_id == self.reject_order_id {\n            Outcome::Reject\n        } else {\n            self.records\n                .lock()\n                .await\n                .push((msg.order_id.clone(), msg.amount));\n            Outcome::Ack\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/// Handler that records which messages were received on the DLQ.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct DlqRecordingHandler {\n    dead_messages: Arc<tokio::sync::Mutex<Vec<SimpleMessage>>>,\n}\n\nimpl DlqRecordingHandler {\n    fn new() -> Self {\n        Self {\n            dead_messages: Arc::new(tokio::sync::Mutex::new(Vec::new())),\n        }\n    }\n\n    async fn dead_messages(&self) -> Vec<SimpleMessage> {\n        self.dead_messages.lock().await.clone()\n    }\n}\n\nimpl MessageHandler<WorkTopic> for DlqRecordingHandler {\n    async fn handle(&self, _msg: SimpleMessage, _meta: MessageMetadata) -> Outcome {\n        Outcome::Ack\n    }\n\n    async fn handle_dead(&self, msg: SimpleMessage, _meta: DeadMessageMetadata) {\n        self.dead_messages.lock().await.push(msg);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify it compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo -q check --features aws-sns-sqs --test sns_sqs_integration`\nExpected: compiles with no errors (0 tests to run yet)\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/sns_sqs_integration.rs Cargo.toml\ngit commit -m \"test: add sns_sqs_integration test harness and topic definitions\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Client Lifecycle Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `tests/sns_sqs_integration.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add client lifecycle tests**\n\nAppend to the test file:\n\n```rust\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Client lifecycle\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn client_connect_and_shutdown() {\n    let broker = TestBroker::start().await;\n    let client = SnsClient::new(&broker.sns_config())\n        .await\n        .expect(\"client should connect\");\n\n    assert!(\n        !client.shutdown_token().is_cancelled(),\n        \"shutdown token should not be cancelled before shutdown\"\n    );\n\n    client.shutdown().await;\n\n    assert!(\n        client.shutdown_token().is_cancelled(),\n        \"shutdown token should be cancelled after shutdown\"\n    );\n}\n\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn client_shutdown_cancels_token() {\n    let broker = TestBroker::start().await;\n    let client = SnsClient::new(&broker.sns_config())\n        .await\n        .expect(\"client should connect\");\n\n    let token = client.shutdown_token();\n    assert!